text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!LanguageOfTheNacirema]]%0a%0a!Philosophy lessons from BAT%0a%0a:Author: saraht%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aPhilosophy lessons from BAT%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aYou can be blind as a BAT. You can run like a BAT out of hell, maybe from an old BAT. In school, it’s probably not best to BAT out assignments the night they’re due – unless you BAT a thousand on your previous assignments. If you’ve done well in the class so far, you might be able to BAT the breeze for the rest of the term. If you like someone, you can ask them out right off the BAT, but they might play a straight BAT to avoid rejecting you. You could also let them know by BATTING your eyelashes at them. In the worst case, your crush might not BAT an eye. In the best case, they could ask you out off their own BAT. You might want to BAT around the idea with their friends to see if there’s a chance your crush also BATs for you. Hopefully, their friends don’t BAT away the idea because they BAT for another person.%0a%0aNacirema culture places a particular emphasis on the flying mammal known as a bat, but also the sport of baseball. They seem to have a negative view of with the animal and feel a deep connection to sport. They describe a lot of their daily life using baseball terminology and actions. They also seem to view everything as a competition, with many of their phrases implying a “me vs. you” conflict. %0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a#foxbegin 210327-190804-266300#%0a(:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a!!!Alternate of BAT %0a-> - sirisha_b%0a(:div1end:) %0a>>messageitem%3c%3c %0aI think another way of looking at BAT could be in a way that shows how eccentric and physical certain aspects of the Nacirema culture are.  With the animal bat, people tend to see it as this small rodent that behaves in an eccentric, bizarre manner, and that could also be used to describe a batty lady or even batting eyelashes to get some sort of attention.  In regards to the object used to hit something, that shows how the Nacirema may get really caught up in something and get very physical to get it out of the way.  When there are a lot of flies around someone, for example, the flies are acting "batty" and annoying and people may swat and bat their arms to get rid of them, so both the insect and the humans have this eccentric, physical quality about them.%0a>>%3c%3c%0a#foxend 210327-190804-266300#%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: A:)%0a(:Category: LanguageOfTheNacirema:)
