diff:1616872084:1616192889:=47,55c47%0a%3c #foxbegin 210327-190804-266300#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Alternate of BAT %0a%3c -> - sirisha_b%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c I think another way of looking at BAT could be in a way that shows how eccentric and physical certain aspects of the Nacirema culture are.  With the animal bat, people tend to see it as this small rodent that behaves in an eccentric, bizarre manner, and that could also be used to describe a batty lady or even batting eyelashes to get some sort of attention.  In regards to the object used to hit something, that shows how the Nacirema may get really caught up in something and get very physical to get it out of the way.  When there are a lot of flies around someone, for example, the flies are acting "batty" and annoying and people may swat and bat their arms to get rid of them, so both the insect and the humans have this eccentric, physical quality about them.%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 210327-190804-266300#%0a---%0a> %0a
